---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import StatusStrip from '../components/StatusStrip.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Getting to Pohnpei — The Garden Island of Micronesia"
  description="How to get to Pohnpei Island, FSM. Flights via United Airlines Island Hopper from Honolulu and Guam, plus Nauru Airlines from Brisbane."
>
  <Nav />
  <StatusStrip />

  <main class="pt-[116px]">
    <section class="py-28 md:py-36 px-6 md:px-24 bg-sand">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <span
          class="font-label text-ochre tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-[11px] font-semibold mb-8 block"
        >
          Plan Your Visit
        </span>
        <h1
          class="font-headline text-basalt text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl leading-[1.02] tracking-tight mb-10"
        >
          Getting to <em class="italic text-ochre">Pohnpei</em>.
        </h1>

        <div class="space-y-8 font-body text-basalt/75 text-[16px] leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Pohnpei International Airport (PNI) sits just outside Kolonia, the
            island's main town. It's small, unhurried, and exactly what you'd
            expect from a place this far from everything.
          </p>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl text-basalt mb-4">By Air</h2>
            <p class="mb-4">
              <strong class="text-basalt">United Airlines Island Hopper</strong> — the
              primary route. Flies between Honolulu and Guam with stops across
              Micronesia, including Pohnpei. Runs several times per week. Most
              visitors connect through Guam or Honolulu.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong class="text-basalt">Nauru Airlines</strong> — operates a
              Brisbane–Pohnpei route via Nauru. A good option if you're coming
              from Australia or the South Pacific.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl text-basalt mb-4">Common Routes</h2>
            <ul class="space-y-2 list-none">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-ochre mt-1">→</span>
                <span><strong class="text-basalt">From the US West Coast:</strong> Fly to Honolulu or Guam, then connect to PNI via Island Hopper.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-ochre mt-1">→</span>
                <span><strong class="text-basalt">From Australia:</strong> Brisbane to Pohnpei via Nauru Airlines.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-ochre mt-1">→</span>
                <span><strong class="text-basalt">From Asia:</strong> Fly to Guam from Manila, Tokyo, Seoul, or Taipei, then connect to PNI.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl text-basalt mb-4">Tips</h2>
            <ul class="space-y-2 list-none">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-ochre mt-1">•</span>
                <span>Always reconfirm flight schedules — routes change seasonally and delays are part of island travel.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-ochre mt-1">•</span>
                <span>Build in a buffer day on either side of your trip. Connections through Guam or Honolulu don't always line up neatly.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-ochre mt-1">•</span>
                <span>Passport must be valid for at least 6 months beyond your travel dates.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-ochre mt-1">•</span>
                <span>Notify your bank before you go. ATMs exist but aren't everywhere.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-16 pt-10 border-t border-basalt/10">
          <p class="font-body text-basalt/55 text-sm mb-6">
            More detailed travel info coming soon — routes, packing lists, and what to expect on arrival.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/#dispatch"
            class="bg-ochre text-white px-8 py-4 font-label uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-xs font-semibold hover:bg-ochre-deep active:scale-95 transition-all inline-block"
          >
            Join the Dispatch for Updates
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
